OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1778595071
OL,3,CDonald Campbell's Bluebird K7
OL,4,Chydroplane returns to Coniston Water
OL,6,FCampbell and his K7 boat became
OL,7,Fsynonymous with Coniston in the 1950s,
OL,8,Fwhen he broke water speed records
OL,9,Fseveral times.
OL,11,FCampbell died after Bluebird K7
OL,12,Fcrashed during a subsequent speed
OL,13,Frecord attempt on Coniston Water in
OL,14,FJanuary 1967.
OL,16,FThe wreckage of the vessel was raised
OL,17,Fin 2001 and painstakingly rebuilt by
OL,18,FThe Bluebird Project in North Shields.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/11
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1778595071
OL,3,CDonald Campbell's Bluebird K7
OL,4,Chydroplane returns to Coniston Water
OL,6,FIt was returned to Coniston in 2024,
OL,7,Fwhere it has since been housed in the
OL,8,Ftown's Ruskin Museum.
OL,10,FTracy Hodgson, Director of the Ruskin
OL,11,FMuseum said: "Since Bluebird K7
OL,12,Freturned to Coniston, we have had
OL,13,Fthousands of extra visitors coming
OL,14,Fspecially to see her in the place that
OL,15,Fis so synonymous with Donald Campbell
OL,16,Fand his successful water speed runs.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/11
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1778595071
OL,3,CDonald Campbell's Bluebird K7
OL,4,Chydroplane returns to Coniston Water
OL,6,F"This festival is the culmination of
OL,7,Fmany months of hard work from the
OL,8,Forganisation team, volunteers and
OL,9,FBluebird supporters, and it will be
OL,10,Ffitting to see her back out on
OL,11,FConiston, almost 60 years on from that
OL,12,Ffateful last speed record attempt.
OL,14,F"The eyes of the world will be on
OL,15,FConiston, and we are keeping
OL,16,Feverything crossed for good weather
OL,17,Fand water conditions to enable decent
OL,18,Frunning speeds, so that everyone who
OL,19,Fmakes the journey to participate in
OL,20,Fthe festival goes home happy."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/11
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1778595071
OL,3,CDonald Campbell's Bluebird K7
OL,4,Chydroplane returns to Coniston Water
OL,6,FDuring the week, Bluebird K7 will be
OL,7,Fpiloted by Dave Warby, with a reserve
OL,8,Fpilot, serving RAF flight instructor
OL,9,FDJ Gibbs, joining later on in the week
OL,10,Fwhen he is released from active
OL,11,Fmilitary duty.
OL,13,FOrganisers have said the plan is to
OL,14,Foperate runs on Coniston as frequently
OL,15,Fas weather and water conditions will
OL,16,Fallow throughout the festival, with
OL,17,Fdaytime activities scheduled Monday to
OL,18,FSunday from 10am to 5pm.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/11
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
