OL,3,CDonald Campbell's Bluebird K7
OL,4,Chydroplane returns to Coniston Water
OL,6,FWho was Donald Campbell, Bluebird's
OL,7,Frecord-breaking pilot?
OL,9,FThe son of Sir Malcolm Campbell, the
OL,10,Fcharismatic and patriotic Donald was
OL,11,Fdestined to follow in his father's
OL,12,Ffootsteps. His father was a world
OL,13,Fspeed record holder on land and water.
OL,14,FSir Malcolm was one of the few record
OL,15,Fbreakers of his era to die of natural
OL,16,Fcauses rather than in a crash.
OL,18,FBetween 1955 and 1964, the younger
OL,19,FCampbell set seven water-speed world
OL,20,Frecords in his Bluebird K7 craft. Four
OL,21,Fof these were on Coniston Water.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/11
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1778595071
OL,3,CDonald Campbell's Bluebird K7
OL,4,Chydroplane returns to Coniston Water
OL,6,FIn July 1964 he claimed the land speed
OL,7,Fprize at Lake Air salt flats in
OL,8,FAustralia, recording a speed of
OL,9,F403mph. He remains the only person to
OL,10,Fbreak the world land and water speed
OL,11,Frecords in the same year.
OL,13,FThree years later, he and Bluebird
OL,14,Fwere back on Coniston Water trying to
OL,15,Freach 300mph. Adverse weather caused
OL,16,Fsevere delays in the record attempt,
OL,17,Fcausing frustration in the team and in
OL,18,Fthe media.
OL,20,FCampbell eventually saw an opportunity
OL,21,Ffor the attempt on 4 January 1967.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G9/11
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
